1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill Nos. 3068 & 3049, Page 39, Section
2 589.417, Line 27, by inserting after all of said line the following:
3
4 "589.770. 1. For purposes of this section, the following terms mean:
5 (1) "Convicted" or "conviction", a finding by a court that an individual is guilty of a
6 criminal offense through adjudication, or entry of a plea of guilty or no contest to the charge by
7 the offender;
8 (2) "Department", the Missouri department of public safety;
9 (3) "Domestic abuse victim", a victim of a felony or class A misdemeanor offense under
10 chapter 565 involving physical injury, threat of physical injury, or sexual assault committed by a
11 family or household member, as defined in section 455.010;
12 (4) "Persistent domestic violence offender", a person who:
13 (a) Has been convicted in this state of an offense committed against a domestic abuse
14 victim; and
15 (b) Has at least one prior conviction for an offense committed against a domestic abuse
16 victim.
17 2. There is hereby created within the department of public safety a registry of persistent
18 domestic violence offenders. The Missouri state highway patrol shall maintain the registry based
19 on information supplied to the department as provided under subsections 3 and 4 of this section
20 and information available to the department from the department of corrections and local law
21 enforcement agencies. The department shall make the registry available for public inquiry on
22 the internet.
23 3. The registry shall consist of each persistent domestic violence offender's name, date of
24 birth, domestic violence offense, conviction date, county or counties of such convictions, and a
25 current photograph of the persistent domestic violence offender. If available after reasonable
26 inquiry, the court clerk shall provide the department with a copy of each persistent domestic
27 violence offender's driver's license, or other state or federal identification, and such other
28 identifying data as the department determines is necessary to properly identify the persistent
29 domestic violence offender and exclude innocent persons. However, the registry available for
Action Taken___________________________________________ Date __________________
